                    \u003Csupport>\n                                    \u003Cp>Four fragments of a lead lamina, inscribed on one side, of which fragments 2-3 join, and can be related to fr. 1; fr. 4 remains unconnected but part of the whole. Frag. 1, H 3.5 cm, W 1 cm; frag. 2, H 2.6 cm, W 1.7 cm; frag. 3 , H 2.4 cm, W 1.5 cm; frag. 4, H 2.3 cm, W 2 cm.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.metal.lead\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/108.html\">lead\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.lamina\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/145.html\">lamina\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.complete\"/>\n                            \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.engraved\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/3\">Engraved\u003C/rs>\n                                    \u003Cp>Fragment 1 shows a consistent left margin to the text; vacats at the end of some lines on fragment 3 show an irregular right margin to the text.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.complete\"/>\n                                \u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp> open omega, sigma with diverging top and bottom strokes.\u